    <segment id="1" parent="2" relname="background">I looked online for the proper definition. </segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="8" relname="span">

&quot;Usability ? Intuitiveness 

Gist: High probability in % that operator will within a specified time from deciding the need to perform the task (without reference to handbooks or help facility) find a way to accomplish their desired task.
Scale: Probability that a TRAINED operator will find a way to do whatever they need to do, without reference to any written instructions (i.e. on paper or on- line in the system, other than help or guidance instructions offered by the system on the screen during operation of the system) within a specified time of deciding that there is a necessity to perform the task.
TRAINED: any system user approved or certified with the officially approved amount of training for their level of task and responsibility.
REGULAR TASK: a task that is performed once per day
IRREGULAR TASK: a task that is performed less frequently than once per day&quot;</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="2" relname="justify">



Source: Garbutt R. (2003). A BEST PRACTICE GUIDE TO DIGITIZATION USER REQUIREMENTS. Retrieved on February 12, 2004, from http://www.ams.mod.uk </segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="5" relname="background">

